Definition: formally reject or disavow a formerly held belief, usually under pressure
Example: He retracted his earlier statements about his religion; She abjured her beliefs
Synonyms: noun, communication, abjuration, person, abjurer, recant, recantation, forswear, act, forswearing, retract, retraction, resile, renounce, formally, reject, or, disavow, a, formerly, held, belief, usually, under, pressure, He, retracted, his, earlier, statements, about, religion, She, abjured, her, beliefs
Frame: 2,8
Category: verb.communication
